<HEADLINE>
Pakistan says it will adhere to nuclear test ban treaty
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   UNITED NATIONS (AP) _ Pakistan's prime minister said Wednesday
his country would unilaterally adhere to the nuclear test ban
treaty, but called on international pressure to force rival India
to do the same.
	   Nawaz Sharif said Pakistan was ready for adherance before a
nuclear conference in September 1999 if international sanctions
were speedily lifted.
